 driver drives 2 DC motors or 1 stepper up to 46V 2A#Wiring Notes#{3}":[85,85],"#L298N dual H-bridge motor driver drives 2 DC motors or 1 stepper up to 46V 2A#Wiring Notes#{4}":[86,86],"#L298N dual H-bridge motor driver drives 2 DC motors or 1 stepper up to 46V 2A#Wiring Notes#{5}":[87,87],"#L298N dual H-bridge motor driver drives 2 DC motors or 1 stepper up to 46V 2A#Wiring Notes#{6}":[88,89],"#L298N dual H-bridge motor driver drives 2 DC motors or 1 stepper up to 46V 2A#Warnings":[90,108],"#L298N dual H-bridge motor driver drives 2 DC motors or 1 stepper up to 46V 2A#Warnings#{1}":[92,92],"#L298N dual H-bridge motor driver drives 2 DC motors or 1 stepper up to 46V 2A#Warnings#{2}":[93,93],"#L298N dual H-bridge motor driver drives 2 DC motors or 1 stepper up to 46V 2A#Warnings#{3}":[94,94],"#L298N dual H-bridge motor driver drives 2 DC motors or 1 stepper up to 46V 2A#Warnings#{4}":[95,96],"#L298N dual H-bridge motor driver drives 2 DC motors or 1 stepper up to 46V 2A#Warnings#{5}":[97,99],"#L298N dual H-bridge motor driver drives 2 DC motors or 1 stepper up to 46V 2A#Warnings#{6}":[100,100],"#L298N dual H-bridge motor driver drives 2 DC motors or 1 stepper up to 46V 2A#Warnings#{7}":[101,102],"#L298N dual H-bridge motor driver drives 2 DC motors or 1 stepper up to 46V 2A#Warnings#{8}":[103,105],"#L298N dual H-bridge motor driver drives 2 DC motors or 1 stepper up to 46V 2A#Warnings#{9}":[106,106],"#L298N dual H-bridge motor driver drives 2 DC motors or 1 stepper up to 46V 2A#Warnings#{10}":[107,108]},"outlinks":[{"title":"actuators","target":"actuators","line":3},{"title":"shields","target":"shields","line":3},{"title":"28byj-48-5v-unipolar-stepper-motor-with-uln2003-driver","target":"28byj-48-5v-unipolar-stepper-motor-with-uln2003-driver","line":31},{"title":"arduino-mega-2560-is-a-54-io-5v-board-with-4-hardware-uarts","target":"arduino-mega-2560-is-a-54-io-5v-board-with-4-hardware-uarts","line":31},{"title":"arduino-uno-r3-is-a-14-io-5v-board-with-atmega328p-and-usb-b","target":"arduino-uno-r3-is-a-14-io-5v-board-with-atmega328p-and-usb-b","line":31},{"title":"28byj-48-5v-unipolar-stepper-motor-with-uln2003-driver","target":"28byj-48-5v-unipolar-stepper-motor-with-uln2003-driver","line":100},{"title":"max7219-spi-led-driver-controls-8-digits-or-8x8-matrix-with-3-pins","target":"max7219-spi-led-driver-controls-8-digits-or-8x8-matrix-with-3-pins","line":101},{"title":"riorand-zs-x11h-bldc-controller-6-60v-16a-with-hall-sensor-input","target":"riorand-zs-x11h-bldc-controller-6-60v-16a-with-hall-sensor-input","line":103},{"title":"actuators","target":"actuators","line":106},{"title":"shields","target":"shields","line":107}],"metadata":{"description":"The go-to H-bridge for medium-power motor projects — 2A continuous per channel, 46V max, TTL inputs. Gets hot at higher currents, needs heatsink and flyback diodes","topics":["[[actuators]]","[[shields]]"],"status":"verified","quantity":2,"voltage":[5,7,12,24,36,46],"interfaces":["Digital","PWM"],"logic_level":"mixed","logic_notes":"Uses a 5V logic supply, but the IN/EN pins are TTL-threshold inputs so 3.3V MCU outputs usually work. It does not present MCU-safe logic outputs.","manufacturer":"STMicroelectronics","part_number":"L298N","pinout":"Multiwatt15 package:\nPin 1  → Current Sensing A (connect sense resistor to GND)\nPin 2  → Output 1 (motor A terminal 1)\nPin 3  → Output 2 (motor A terminal 2)\nPin 4  → VS (motor supply, up to 46V)\nPin 5  → Input 1 (TTL, bridge A direction)\nPin 6  → Enable A (TTL, PWM for speed control)\nPin 7  → Input 2 (TTL, bridge A direction)\nPin 8  → GND\nPin 9  → VSS (logic supply, 4.5-7V)\nPin 10 → Input 3 (TTL, bridge B direction)\nPin 11 → Enable B (TTL, PWM for speed control)\nPin 12 → Input 4 (TTL, bridge B direction)\nPin 13 → Output 3 (motor B terminal 1)\nPin 14 → Output 4 (motor B terminal 2)\nPin 15 → Current Sensing B (connect sense resistor to GND)\n","max_current_per_channel":"2A DC, 2.5A repetitive, 3A peak","total_current_limit":"4A total","compatible_with":["[[arduino-uno-r3-is-a-14-io-5v-board-with-atmega328p-and-usb-b]]","[[arduino-mega-2560-is-a-54-io-5v-board-with-4-hardware-uarts]]","[[28byj-48-5v-unipolar-stepper-motor-with-uln2003-driver]]"],"used_in":[],"warnings":["Needs external flyback diodes (fast recovery, trr < 200ns) on all motor outputs","High saturation voltage drop: 1.8-4.9V total — at 12V motor supply you lose up to 5V to the driver","25W max dissipation — NEEDS heatsink at currents above 0.5A","Separate logic supply (VSS) required: 4.5-7V with 100nF cap to GND","Motor supply (VS) needs 100nF cap to GND"],"datasheet_url":"Datasheets/l298n.pdf"},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[[56,69]],"key":"docs/parts/l298n-dual-h-bridge-motor-driver-drives-2-dc-motors-or-1-stepper-up-to-46v-2a.md"},"smart_blocks:docs/parts/l298n-dual-h-bridge-motor-driver-drives-2-dc-motors-or-1-stepper-up-to-46v-2a.md#---frontmatter---": {"path":null,"last_embed":{"hash":"3jd65w","at":1776210316464},"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.05044804,0.01670057,0.00952947,-0.04454254,-0.02359596,0.02318769,-0.00553789,0.05832194,0.01916219,-0.00588572,-0.01462916,-0.07382738,0.03801408,0.04575758,-0.01469772,0.00922426,0.00115987,-0.03337479,0.04813226,0.03127089,0.07044604,-0.06296463,0.0304149,0.02087819,0.04224334,0.06195104,-0.0018171,0.01764416,-0.00586675,-0.25235468,0.02122568,0.03797377,-0.05412815,-0.00677952,-0.04459633,-0.05904185,-0.05617896,-0.02221369,-0.01263253,-0.01862015,0.03529616,-0.01857947,0.03325766,-0.07647663,-0.00545087,-0.0042201,-0.02112572,-0.02810786,0.03551019,-0.0581844,0.0039627,0.00646402,0.05370926,-0.05006331,0.01134829,0.04934874,0.00420243,0.06856084,0.00798806,0.01999566,0.05949392,0.03339298,-0.21064587,0.08911109,0.02249001,0.00524445,-0.03854764,0.00986707,0.03377444,0.12996513,0.00127187,-0.0353935,-0.00019605,0.02108588,0.02426443,-0.0149193,0.00627785,-0.04684005,-0.00692141,-0.00334982,0.02919016,-0.02284487,-0.06598496,-0.00821585,-0.065